    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>The Colours from the Grey event of Pravega is a biology puzzle. Tushar has designed the game such that each team starts on one end of a <b>NxN</b> grid and answer the questions which are at the other lattice points. The contestants are at position (0,0) on the grid and there is one question on each point <b>(i,j)</b> where <b>0 \u2264 i,j \u2264 N, (i,j) \u2260 (0,0)</b>.</p>\n<p>The teams choose any question on the grid and answer them. However, they can only answer a question directly visible to them and not hidden behind another question. Now, Tushar is wondering what is the maximum number of questions available to answer for a team at any instant during the game. Can you help him?</p>\n<p><b>\n<p>Input:</p>\n<p></p></b></p>\n<p>The first line of the input gives the number of test cases <b>T</b>.</p>\n<p>The next <b>T</b> lines contain a single number <b>N</b>, the size of the grid. (the grid starts from (0,0))</p>\n<p><b>\n<p>Output:</p>\n<p></p></b></p>\n<p>The output to each test case should be on a new line. On each of the <b>T</b> lines there should be one integer which is the maximum number of questions available to answer.</p>\n<p><b>\n<p>Input constraints:</p>\n<p></p></b></p>\n<p>0&lt; <b>T</b> \u226410000</p>\n<p>0&lt; <b>N</b> &lt;10000</p>\n<p><b>\n<p>Sample input:</p>\n<p></p></b><br />\n2<br />\n1<br />\n2</p>\n<p><b>\n<p>Sample output:</p>\n<p></p></b><br />\n3<br />\n5</p>\n",
